---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { SITE } from "../consts";
---

<Base
  title="About"
  description="An honest note: this is early, evidence-based, and seeking a research partner and pilots."
>
  <section class="wrap intro">
    <p class="eyebrow rise rise-1">About</p>
    <h1 class="rise rise-2">An honest note on where this is.</h1>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap body measure">
    <p>
      The Human-Core Initiative is early. It is a founding proposal and a first
      set of written, pilotable materials, not a finished system and not a
      guarantee. We would rather say that plainly than oversell it.
    </p>

    <p>
      What it is: a free, open synthesis of what the science of learning already
      shows, extended with the one dimension the existing efforts predate, the
      arrival of capable AI, pointed deliberately at empowering teachers and
      teaching children rather than at surveilling them. It is owned by no
      company and adoptable by anyone.
    </p>

    <p>
      We hold our claims to the evidence. Effect sizes in education are usually
      modest, context matters, and the largest single lever is not a tool but a
      knowledgeable, well-supported teacher and an engaged adult at home. The AI
      evidence is new and moving fast, so we treat the specific tools as
      provisional and the underlying principle, that the child must do the
      thinking, as durable. We will publish what fails as openly as what works.
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      <h2>What we are looking for</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>A research partner.</strong> An institution to validate and
          stress-test the pedagogy, so it is more than one practitioner's
          conviction.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Pilots.</strong> Small, well-observed first runs with
          volunteer teachers, because the evidence is clear that programs lose
          much of their effect when scaled carelessly. We earn scale by proving
          the model works small.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p>
      If you are a teacher, a school, a researcher, or a funder who wants to help
      prove or disprove this in the open, the work lives in the
      <a href={SITE.repo} rel="noopener">public repository</a>, and contributions
      and critique are welcome. Start with the
      <a href="/resources">free resources</a> and the
      <a href="/principles">principles</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .intro { padding-top: 3.5rem; }
  .intro h1 { font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3.4rem); margin: 0.6rem 0 0; }
  .body { margin-top: 2rem; font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-ink); }
  .body > * + * { margin-top: 1.2rem; }
  .body p { color: var(--color-ink-soft); margin: 0; }
  .callout h2 { font-size: 1.3rem; margin: 0 0 0.8rem; }
  .callout ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.1rem; list-style: none; display: grid; gap: 0.7rem; }
  .callout li { position: relative; padding-left: 1.1rem; color: var(--color-ink-soft); }
  .callout li::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0; top: 0.62em;
    width: 0.42rem; height: 0.42rem;
    background: var(--color-pine);
    border-radius: 2px;
    transform: rotate(45deg);
  }
  .callout strong { color: var(--color-ink); }
</style>
